<LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
<TITLE>rgb2hsv</TITLE>
<TYPE>SIVP Toolbox</TYPE>
<DATE>August, 2006</DATE>
<SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="rgb2hsv">Convert a RGB image to the equivalent HSV image.</SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
<CALLING_SEQUENCE>
   <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>HSV = rgb2hsv(RGB)</CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
</CALLING_SEQUENCE>
<PARAM>
<PARAM_INDENT>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>RGB</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   A RGB image (hypermat), the dimension of <TT>RGB</TT> should be <TT>M x N x 3</TT>.
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>HSV</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   Output image, which has the same size as <TT>RGB</TT> and type of double.
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
</PARAM_INDENT>
</PARAM>
<DESCRIPTION>
<P>
   <TT>rgb2hsv</TT> convert a RGB image to the equivalent HSV image using:</P>
<DESCRIPTION_INDENT>
  <DESCRIPTION_ITEM>
    <TT>V = max(R,G,B)</TT>
  </DESCRIPTION_ITEM> 
  <DESCRIPTION_ITEM>
    <TT>S = (V-min(R,G,B))/V</TT> if V&lt;&gt;0, 0 otherwise
  </DESCRIPTION_ITEM> 
  <DESCRIPTION_ITEM>
    <TT>H = </TT>
    <DESCRIPTION_INDENT>
      <DESCRIPTION_ITEM>
	<TT>(G - B)/6/S</TT>, if V=R; 
      </DESCRIPTION_ITEM> 
      <DESCRIPTION_ITEM>
	<TT>1/2+(B - R)/6/S</TT>,  if V=G; 
      </DESCRIPTION_ITEM> 
      <DESCRIPTION_ITEM>
	<TT>2/3+(R - G)/6/S</TT>,  if V=B.
      </DESCRIPTION_ITEM> 
    </DESCRIPTION_INDENT>
  </DESCRIPTION_ITEM> 
</DESCRIPTION_INDENT>

<P>
  Supported classes: INT8, UINT8, INT16, UINT16, INT32, DOUBLE.
If <TT>RGB</TT> is not a double image, it will be converted to double image first
in the procedure. 
</P>
 
</DESCRIPTION>
<EXAMPLE><![CDATA[

    RGB = imread('lena.png');
    HSV = rgb2hsv(RGB);
    RGB = hsv2rgb(HSV);
    imshow(RGB);

]]></EXAMPLE>

